ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: congruent condition
Category number
Reaction Time
Accuracy on the current trial of the missing feature (MF) task
Notes: 0 = Incorrect; 1 = Correct; 999 = Explicit feature selection task

ElementDescription: Trial number
Trial Identifier
Structure of the current category; see notes
Trial type
Notes: 1=Core; 2=Peripheral; 3=Catch; Note: Catch trials serve as attention checks, coded as ''Core'' for explicit feature selection trial

ElementDescription: First visual feature of trial stimulus
Notes: 1=antennae1; 2=antennae2; 3=antennae3; 4=wings1; 5=arms1; 6=wings2; 7=legs1; 8=tail1; 9=feet1; 10=spots1; 11=spots2; 999 = Explicit feature selection trial with all features shown

ElementDescription: Second visual feature of trial stimulus
Notes: 1=antennae1; 2=antennae2; 3=antennae3; 4=wings1; 5=arms1; 6=wings2; 7=legs1; 8=tail1; 9=feet1; 10=spots1; 11=spots2; 999 = Explicit feature selection trial with all features shown

ElementDescription: Third visual feature of trial stimulus
Notes: 1=antennae1; 2=antennae2; 3=antennae3; 4=wings1; 5=arms1; 6=wings2; 7=legs1; 8=tail1; 9=feet1; 10=spots1; 11=spots2; 999 = Explicit feature selection trial with all features shown

ElementDescription: Fourth visual feature of trial stimulus
Notes: 1=antennae1; 2=antennae2; 3=antennae3; 4=wings1; 5=arms1; 6=wings2; 7=legs1; 8=tail1; 9=feet1; 10=spots1; 11=spots2; 999 = Explicit feature selection trial with all features shown

ElementDescription: Fifth visual feature of trial stimulus
Notes: 1=antennae1; 2=antennae2; 3=antennae3; 4=wings1; 5=arms1; 6=wings2; 7=legs1; 8=tail1; 9=feet1; 10=spots1; 11=spots2; 999 = Explicit feature selection trial with all features shown

ElementDescription: First of two potential response options (Correct answer on the missing feature trial)
Notes: Randomized structural assignment of each feature; 999 = Explicit feature selection trial with all features shown

ElementDescription: Second of two potential response options (Incorrect answer on the missing feature trial)
Notes: Randomized structural assignment of each feature; 999 = Explicit feature selection trial with all features shown

ElementDescription: Accuracy on the current trial of the explicit feature selection task
Notes: Number of correct features selected out of 3; 999 = Missing feature trial
